For the latest news, visit the SparForte web site.

Objective: Foundation for value meta labels

Known Issues

CHANGES SINCE 2.6.3

1. Fix: For constant specifications, when the specification is fulfilled the type of the assigned value is now verified with the type of the constant.  Previously the type was not verified.

2. Fix: command type variables must contain paths to files in a secure directory.

3. Fix: arrays with limited or constant elements cannot be rearranged by sorting, shuffling, rotating, shifting, or flipping.  to_array also will no longer write to limited or constant array elements.

4. Fix: malformed numeric literals like "123_" no longer throw an Ada exception.

5. Fix: Added missing entry for doubly_linked_lists.last to the documentation.

6. Fix: vectors package documentation has several corrections.

7. Fix: vectors.delete calculates the vector index correctly.

8. Fix: vectors.delete no longer allows a count with a cursor because of SparForte's meta data label implementation.

9. New: vectors.no_index, vectors.find_index, vectors.reverse_find_index, vectors.has_element, vectors.assign, vectors.decrement, vectors.increment, vectors.to_index. [positive and negative tests needed]

10. Fix: dynamic_hash_table package documentation correction.

11. Fix: doubly linked lists assemble / disassemble are restricted under pragma ada_95.

12. Enhancement: better error messages for procedure / function mismatches.

13. Enhancement: better error messages for some edge cases like using a generic type as a shell command.

14. Refactor: world package was refactored especially moving the symbol table into a separate file.

15. Fix: documentation corrected for doubly_linked_lists.insert_before, cgi package, calendar.to_julian.

16. New: enum.pos / enum.val [negative tests needed].

17. New: added type calendar.julian_date.

18. Fix: out parameters with resource variables won't  create new resources when one is already attached to the variable.

19. New: tags package.  Name may change.  [docs needed][tests needed][name may change].

20. Refactor: cgi package largely rewritten but no new functionality. [testing needed]

21. Change: performance static metrics are right-justified.

22. Fix: command_line.argument has an error message with a position is out-of-range rather than reporting an unexpected exception.

23. Fix: exit status codes are limited to range 0..255 and a new error message in command_line.set_exit_status when a status code is out-of-range.

24. Fix: directory_operations.dir_name missing entry added to package documentation.

25. Change: directory_operations.change_dir now updates the PWD and OLDPWD variables for Bourne shell compatibility, even though the Ada version does not update these variables.

26. Fix: array out parameters now type checked against their element type not the array type.

27. Fix: gnat.crc32.initialize() no longer checks the parameter type twice.

28. Fix: dbm package calls using an uninitialized query object no longer show an error message with "connection" instead of "query".

29. Fix: non-generic in out parameters to built-in package subprograms should be able to use an array element as well as a scalar variable.

30. Fix: array index zero handling fixed for out and in out parameters.  That is, no longer treats a reference to a(0) as a scalar variable a.

31. Fix: generic in out parameters to built-in package subprograms should be able to use an array element as well as a scalar variable. [tests needed]

32. Fix. l10n functions returning a natural 255 no longer raise an exception.  Returns 255 for a -1 signed byte.

33. Fix: logs.mode, logs.width no longer run during a syntax check.

34. New: pragma meta_label to assign meta labels to stdin, stdout and stderr. [Docs needed] [Tests needed]

35. Fix: added missing logs.width function to logs documentation.

36. Change: numerics.expr and trig functions now report detailed errors instead of an unexpected exceptions.

37. Change: restriction( no_external_commands ) also disallows os.system().

38. Fix: where possible stats package subprograms no longer have an array empty error with arrays of one element.

39. Fix: missing parameter in get_immediate added to documentation.

40. Fix: Most Text_IO subprograms tested to support arrays of files.  is_open is now an in_out mode parameter for this reason.

41. Fix: current_input, current_output and current_error support renamings and arrays elements.

42. Fix: initialization of renamings no longer point to a scalar value but to a scalar or array element.  (Probably overridden by higher level functions but should be correct here.)

43. Fix: when logging to standard error, the logs package uses the end-of-line for your operating system, rather than a line feed.

44. Fix: get_line reads from current input by default not standard input.

45. New: spar --sbom/-B displays build dependencies (Software Bill of Lading, SBOM).  Tested on Ubuntu, Raspberry Pi, Arch, FreeBSD.  Licenses not available on all systems.

46. Fix: fixed cursor issue in btree get_first function.

47. Fix: fix for btree good regression tests.

48. Fix: broken custom command prompt fixed.

49. Change: a short bug report message appears when an uncaught exception is raised to the main program.

50. Change: the provision.sh script updated for FreeBSD 15.

51. New: pragma annotate( release_date, "string" ).

52. New: added "make sbom" to gather a full sbom when building from sources".

53. New: pragma error_processor [Tests needed]

54. New: basic C type names such as "int", "long" "char", "bool" will have a unique error message if type are not defined.

55. Fix: error pointer was adjusted by -1 but may still have other issues.

